, they are lighter than the usual furniture and require less maintenance. You can have breakfast on this folding table and later set it aside on the wall when you want more floor space. Decorate your balcony with convertible furniture to get the most out of a small space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095100\/home-balcony-decoration-with-folding-furniture.jpg\" alt=\"Home balcony decoration where folding furniture can free up extra space\" class=\"wp-image-39560\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095100\/home-balcony-decoration-with-folding-furniture.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095100\/home-balcony-decoration-with-folding-furniture-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095100\/home-balcony-decoration-with-folding-furniture-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095100\/home-balcony-decoration-with-folding-furniture-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Chic fold-up furniture to maximise balcony space<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Plants In Colourful Pots Are Great Balcony Decor Items<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Decorating a balcony on a budget? Fill up your balcony space with bright and colourful decor items to instantly create a fun vibrant look. You can add bright rugs and cushions to your existing furniture to turn this area into a cheerful corner of your home. You can also add colour through planters and hanging pots as shown below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095035\/balcony-decoration-with-plants-colourful-pots.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony decoration with plants in colorful pots hanging on the wall creates a vibrant look\" class=\"wp-image-39556\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095035\/balcony-decoration-with-plants-colourful-pots.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095035\/balcony-decoration-with-plants-colourful-pots-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095035\/balcony-decoration-with-plants-colourful-pots-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095035\/balcony-decoration-with-plants-colourful-pots-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Transform your balcony on a budget with colours<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create A Reading Nook For Simple Balcony Decoration<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This one is for the ardent readers. A great idea for <strong>balcony decoration<\/strong> is to convert the space into a designated reading corner. This rustic-style balcony features a grey brick wall with a tall bookshelf and a small adjoining bench. Both offer extra storage space through closed cabinets. You can add a few hanging flower pots and cushions to create a cheerful vibe. Grab a book, put your feet up and immerse yourself in your favourite fiction.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095021\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-reading-nooks.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony decoration ideas with a designated reading corner\" class=\"wp-image-39554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095021\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-reading-nooks.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095021\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-reading-nooks-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095021\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-reading-nooks-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095021\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-reading-nooks-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A calm reading spot for the bibliophiles<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Place A Sofa For A Simple Balcony Decoration<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Who said sofas are only meant for the living room? If you\u2019re looking for something more elaborate for your home balcony decoration, adding a sofa is a great option. A nice sofa to relax on and a stunning view, what more do you need? If you\u2019re short on space, a cosy little couch to be able to sit back and unwind works well in small balconies. Adding some wall shelves to display artefacts or succulents is also a popular balcony wall decor idea.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095124\/simple-balcony-decoration-with-sofa.jpg\" alt=\"Simple balcony decoration with a cozy couch to sit back, unwind and enjoy the view\" class=\"wp-image-39564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095124\/simple-balcony-decoration-with-sofa.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095124\/simple-balcony-decoration-with-sofa-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095124\/simple-balcony-decoration-with-sofa-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095124\/simple-balcony-decoration-with-sofa-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Enjoy the view while lounging on your sofa<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Fairy Lights Are The Best Budget Balcony Decoration<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking for balcony decoration with lights, fairy lights are the way to go. They are a fail-safe way to deck up your balcony and are bound to give it a glamorous vibe. Use them vertically to create a drape or loop them around the railing \u2014 either way, it gives your outdoor space a warm glow.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095000\/balcony-decoration-fairy-lights.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony decoration lights with fairy lights are the way to go\" class=\"wp-image-39551\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095000\/balcony-decoration-fairy-lights.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095000\/balcony-decoration-fairy-lights-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095000\/balcony-decoration-fairy-lights-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095000\/balcony-decoration-fairy-lights-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Go all out and deck up your balcony for festivals<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Balcony Makeover Ideas To&nbsp; Make The Most Of Your Outdoor Space<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The above balcony decoration ideas are easy to execute and don\u2019t require much effort. But if you\u2019re looking for a complete makeover, here are some balcony makeover ideas to transform it into a chic outdoor space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Balcony Makeover With Plants<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking to give your small balcony a green twist, create a vertical garden. A green wall is your best bet when the floor space on your balcony is limited. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/vertical-garden-design-ideas\/\">Vertical gardens<\/a> help in creating a tranquil atmosphere, right at home. They are visually appealing and please the eyes and soul too!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095014\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-plants.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony decoration ideas with plants place vertically on a wall to create a tranquil atmosphere\" class=\"wp-image-39553\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095014\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-plants.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095014\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-plants-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095014\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-plants-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095014\/balcony-decoration-ideas-with-plants-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A biophilic balcony with minimalistic cane furniture<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Simple Balcony Makeover With Wall Shelves<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Stuck with an empty wall? A spare wall means a blank canvas and more storage space. Decorate your balcony wall with stylish hanging shelves that can be used to display d\u00e9cor items or small plants. If you have a home workstation on your balcony like the one in this image, you can use the wall shelves for books and stationery items.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095047\/balcony-wall-decor-shelves.jpg\" alt=\"Balcony wall decor with shelves\" class=\"wp-image-39558\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095047\/balcony-wall-decor-shelves.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095047\/balcony-wall-decor-shelves-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095047\/balcony-wall-decor-shelves-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095047\/balcony-wall-decor-shelves-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Spruce up a blank wall and add storage with shelves<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">An Apartment Balcony Makeover Into A Cosy Dining Space<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you have a small or swanky outdoor space, you can easily turn it into an outdoor dining area. Setting up a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/dining-room-interiors\/dining-table-designs\/\">dining table<\/a> on the balcony will not only ensure that everyday meals are looked forward to more than ever, but in the case of bigger balconies, it\u2019s also a great arrangement for having some guests over.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094941\/apartment-balcony-decorating-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Set up a dining table as your apartment balcony decorating ideas for fun family gatherings\" class=\"wp-image-39548\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094941\/apartment-balcony-decorating-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094941\/apartment-balcony-decorating-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094941\/apartment-balcony-decorating-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094941\/apartment-balcony-decorating-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A colourful dining table for fun family gatherings<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Flower Garden Is Ideal For A Small Balcony Makeover On A Budget<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Even the smallest of balconies can accommodate a pretty little flower garden. This small balcony with multiple flowering plants across the railing ensures your outdoor space always feels like a haven away from the hustle and bustle of the city. The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/foldable-furniture\/\">foldable furniture<\/a> helps make the most of the small space. Invest in some cool planters and let your balcony garden blossom!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095130\/small-balcony-decoration-ideas-with-flower-garden.jpg\" alt=\"Small balcony decoration ideas with multiple flowering plants\" class=\"wp-image-39565\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095130\/small-balcony-decoration-ideas-with-flower-garden.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095130\/small-balcony-decoration-ideas-with-flower-garden-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095130\/small-balcony-decoration-ideas-with-flower-garden-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095130\/small-balcony-decoration-ideas-with-flower-garden-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Add beauty to your balcony with a flower garden<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Looking for affordable designer home interiors on EMI\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/08180949\/looking-for-affordable-designer-home-interiors-on-emi.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Budget Balcony Makeover With A Vegetable Garden<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cultivating your own little vegetable patch on your balcony is one of the most satisfying experiences ever. Use that outdoor space to grow your own vegetable garden and save money on buying vegetables. Take inspiration from this balcony that utilises the vertical space for a small vegetable garden. The pots are neatly placed on a blue cabinet that comes in handy to stow gardening essentials.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095053\/budget-balcony-decoration-with-vegetable-garden.jpg\" alt=\"Budget balcony decoration where you can cultivate your little vegetable patch\" class=\"wp-image-39559\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095053\/budget-balcony-decoration-with-vegetable-garden.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095053\/budget-balcony-decoration-with-vegetable-garden-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095053\/budget-balcony-decoration-with-vegetable-garden-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095053\/budget-balcony-decoration-with-vegetable-garden-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A neat and private vegetable garden on the balcony<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Enhance The View From Your Balcony With Glass Railings<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Balcony makeovers don\u2019t always involve populating the space with furniture or decor items. If your balcony opens out to a great view of the city, you can add to its beauty by decorating this space with glass railings. This <strong>balcony makeover<\/strong> creates an optimal setting to enjoy the brilliant view outside. The floor lamp and pendant light add a glowing effect to the space, making it the perfect spot for relaxing in the evening.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095106\/home-balcony-decoration-with-glass-railing.jpg\" alt=\"Home balcony decoration with glass railing enhances the view\" class=\"wp-image-39561\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095106\/home-balcony-decoration-with-glass-railing.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095106\/home-balcony-decoration-with-glass-railing-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095106\/home-balcony-decoration-with-glass-railing-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095106\/home-balcony-decoration-with-glass-railing-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Glass railings on the balcony look luxurious<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use Patterned Tiles For Your Apartment\u2019s Balcony Makeover<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Give your balcony a fresh look with the help of unique floor tiles. Take this balcony, for example. The black and white checkered floor tiles add interest to the space, and the use of minimal furniture makes sure they stand out. The grey chest of drawers and floating shelves offer storage space for books, candles, decor items, gardening essentials, and other knick-knacks. Just get your favourite chair out and enjoy your morning tea from this balcony!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094948\/apartment-balcony-decor-with-patterned-tiles.jpg\" alt=\"Apartment balcony decor floor with patterned tiles to create a lasting impression\" class=\"wp-image-39549\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094948\/apartment-balcony-decor-with-patterned-tiles.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094948\/apartment-balcony-decor-with-patterned-tiles-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094948\/apartment-balcony-decor-with-patterned-tiles-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094948\/apartment-balcony-decor-with-patterned-tiles-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Floor tiles that create a lasting impression<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Give Your Balcony A Green Makeover<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are few things that give the kind of satisfaction akin to walking barefoot on lush green grass. But how do you bring the feel of garden grass into a balcony? By using artificial turf on your balcony floor. This apartment balcony features artificial turf flooring and a wooden tile wall that together make you feel close to nature.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094954\/balcony-decoration-artificial-turf.jpg\" alt=\"A balcony decoration floor with artificial turf and a wooden tile wall together makes it feel close to nature\" class=\"wp-image-39550\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094954\/balcony-decoration-artificial-turf.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094954\/balcony-decoration-artificial-turf-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094954\/balcony-decoration-artificial-turf-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24094954\/balcony-decoration-artificial-turf-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Feel close to nature with this balcony makeover idea<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Turn Your Balcony Into A Workstation<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you work from home, why not add a little bit of fresh air to the routine? Get a modular study table setup, add a few open box shelves to store books and artefacts, and throw in a bit of green. Your balcony will become the perfect change of scene for you to work out of! In this balcony makeover, we\u2019ve added an extra bench with the workstation for extra seating and storage space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095112\/how-to-decorate-balcony-with-workstation.jpg\" alt=\"How to decorate balcony with workstation\" class=\"wp-image-39562\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095112\/how-to-decorate-balcony-with-workstation.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095112\/how-to-decorate-balcony-with-workstation-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095112\/how-to-decorate-balcony-with-workstation-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095112\/how-to-decorate-balcony-with-workstation-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A balcony turned into a compact home office<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a free design consultation from design cafe\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/27144955\/get-free-design-consultation.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Balcony Makeover Into A Party Spot<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Having friends over for fun Friday nights is bound to get interesting with an amazing outdoor setup. Check out this apartment balcony makeover to create the ideal house party spot. The bookshelf has a concealed rack to store your wine collection. A hanging glass rack helps in keeping things organised. The bar counter with stools, the sofa, and multiple other seating options easily accommodate a lot of guests, making your party a great hit!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095041\/balcony-makeover-into-party-spot.jpg\" alt=\"Make your balcony makeover into a party spot with a bar setup\" class=\"wp-image-39557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095041\/balcony-makeover-into-party-spot.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095041\/balcony-makeover-into-party-spot-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095041\/balcony-makeover-into-party-spot-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/24095041\/balcony-makeover-into-party-spot-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Make weekends at home fun with a balcony bar setup<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope you enjoyed reading these balcony makeover ideas. How would you like to decorate your balcony space? <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">Contact us<\/a> and let us know!<\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n   